description:
&lt;p&gt;Job title – Midwifery Practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Area of Work - Birth Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employer – Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Department – Women’s and Sexual Health&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location –Inner London (UHL Birth Centre)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pay Band – Agenda for change (Increments include higher cost of living allowance)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date – 15.11.20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have you been qualified for two years or more? Are you a champion of normality? Would you like to join our dynamic award winning team at Lewisham Birth Centre who are 100% focused on providing woman centred care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lewisham Birth Centre is proud to report that we are one of only three midwifery led units in the UK awarded Beacon Site status for leadership by the Midwifery Unit Network in addition; we also received a Patient Safety award in 2018 from Lewisham and Greenwich NHS. Lewisham Birth Centre regularly receives 100% satisfaction rates through the Friends and Family Test from women and families accessing their care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic team members to help us to promote normality. Could this be you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you think the birthing environment makes a difference to women in labour and their positive birth experience? Would you like to come and find out with us? We work in a beautiful low risk birthing environment and want to offer you the chance to be part of a supportive team and have a job that is full of variety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to practice independently, be an autonomous midwife and have the opportunity to work in our state of the art birth centre?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please read the Personal and Job specifications carefully. You should provide evidence in your application of the essential qualities required and why you would be an asset to our Midwifery Team. We test all shortlisted candidates prior to interview on Risk Assessment and Medicines Management. Invites to testing and interview will be sent to Personal e-mail addresses, please ensure one is provided on your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this post will be shortlisted and those successful will be invited to testing.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short listing to be held: W/C 16.11.20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Testing to be held: 24.11.20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews to be held: 01.12.20 (TBC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tracy Thomas, Birth Centre Lead, UHL on tracythomas2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
